\frac{(z+1)}{z(z-4)^3}
0<|z-4|<4
0<|z-4|<4
\frac{1}{1+(\frac{1}{a})}
a
\frac{z-4}{4}=t\implies z=4t+4
|t|<1
\frac{(1+z)}{z(z-4)^3}=\frac{4t+5}{64(4t+4)(t^3)}=\frac{1}{64t^3}+\frac{1}{256t^3(1+t)}\big(=\frac{1}{256t^3}(1-t+t^2-t^3+\cdots)\big)
=\frac{1}{64t^3}+\frac{1}{256t^3}-\frac{1}{256t^2}+\frac{1}{256t}-\frac{1}{256}+\frac{t}{256}+\cdots
=\frac{5}{256t^3}-\frac{1}{256t^2}+\frac{1}{256t}-\frac{1}{256}+\frac{t}{256}+\cdots
t=\frac{(z-4)}{4}
